    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "3 Nephi",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 14,
        "summary": "Jesus commands: Judge not; ask of God; beware of false prophets\u2014He promises salvation to those who do the will of the Father\u2014Compare Matthew 7. About A.D.\u00a034.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "And now it came to pass that when Jesus had spoken these words he turned again to the multitude, and did open his mouth unto them again, saying: Verily, verily, I say unto you, Judge not, that ye be not judged.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 7:1 (1\u201327); JST\u00a0Matt. 7:1\u20132 (Matt. 7:1 note a).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p1",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For with what judgment ye judge, ye shall be judged; and with what measure ye mete, it shall be measured to you again.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Morm. 8:19.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And why beholdest thou the mote that is in thy brother's eye, but considerest not the beam that is in thine own eye?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Or how wilt thou say to thy brother: Let me pull the mote out of thine eye\u2014and behold, a beam is in thine own eye?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou hypocrite, first cast the beam out of thine own eye; and then shalt thou see clearly to cast the mote out of thy brother's eye.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hypocrisy.",
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 8:7 (3\u201311).",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Give not that which is holy unto the dogs, neither cast ye your pearls before swine, lest they trample them under their feet, and turn again and rend you.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Holiness.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Ask, and it shall be given unto you; seek, and ye shall find; knock, and it shall be opened unto you.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 27:29. TG\u00a0Prayer.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Initiative; Objectives.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 41
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For every one that asketh, receiveth; and he that seeketh, findeth; and to him that knocketh, it shall be opened.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Or what man is there of you, who, if his son ask bread, will give him a stone?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Or if he ask a fish, will he give him a serpent?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "If ye then, being evil, know how to give good gifts unto your children, how much more shall your Father who is in heaven give good things to them that ask him?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore, all things whatsoever ye would that men should do to you, do ye even so to them, for this is the law and the prophets.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Benevolence; Compassion; Courtesy.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Enter ye in at the strait gate; for wide is the gate, and broad is the way, which leadeth to destruction, and many there be who go in thereat;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 13:24; 3\u00a0Ne. 27:33.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 132:25.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 63
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Because strait is the gate, and narrow is the way, which leadeth unto life, and few there be that find it.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 9:41; 31:9 (9, 17\u201318); D&C 22:4.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 8:20.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 38
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 7:14; 1\u00a0Ne. 14:12.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 83
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Beware of false prophets, who come to you in sheep's clothing, but inwardly they are ravening wolves.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 23:21 (21\u201332); 2\u00a0Ne. 28:12 (9, 12, 15). TG\u00a0False Prophets.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 24
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Ye shall know them by their fruits. Do men gather grapes of thorns, or figs of thistles?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Col. 1:6; Alma 32:42 (28\u201342); D&C 52:34 (18, 34).",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 34
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Even so every good tree bringeth forth good fruit; but a corrupt tree bringeth forth evil fruit.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 5:41.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A good tree cannot bring forth evil fruit, neither a corrupt tree bring forth good fruit.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Every tree that bringeth not forth good fruit is hewn down, and cast into the fire.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 3:10; Alma 5:36 (36\u201341); D&C 97:7.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 24
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore, by their fruits ye shall know them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 7:17 (16\u201320); 12:33; Luke 6:43 (43\u201345); Moro. 7:5.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 26
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Not every one that saith unto me, Lord, Lord, shall enter into the kingdom of heaven; but he that doeth the will of my Father who is in heaven.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Jn. 2:17.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 57
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Many will say to me in that day: Lord, Lord, have we not prophesied in thy name, and in thy name have cast out devils, and in thy name done many wonderful works?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 5:17.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And then will I profess unto them: I never knew you; depart from me, ye that work iniquity.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 7:23.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 5:13; 26:25 (24\u201327); D&C 112:26.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 47
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 119:115; Luke 13:27.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore, whoso heareth these sayings of mine and doeth them, I will liken him unto a wise man, who built his house upon a rock\u2014",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Rock.",
                        "start": 124,
                        "end": 128
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the rain descended, and the floods came, and the winds blew, and beat upon that house; and it fell not, for it was founded upon a rock.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 26:6; Hel. 5:12.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 12:7.",
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 102
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And every one that heareth these sayings of mine and doeth them not shall be likened unto a foolish man, who built his house upon the sand\u2014",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Foolishness.",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 99
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 11:40.",
                        "start": 134,
                        "end": 138
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the rain descended, and the floods came, and the winds blew, and beat upon that house; and it fell, and great was the fall of it.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}